---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="42 Holborn Case Study">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Top Bar Navigation -->
    <div class="text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono border-b border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pb-4">
      <a href="/work" class="hover:text-[#FAFAFA] transition-colors">← Back to Work</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Header Section -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider">
        <span>Professional Work</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>2023</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        42 Holborn
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "A custom WordPress site built to handle client constraints and local business details."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Project Snapshot -->
    <section class="border-y border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] py-6 text-xs font-mono text-[#A1A1AA] flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div>Role: <span class="text-white">Full Stack Engineer</span></div>
      <div>Duration: <span class="text-white">Duration: 1 Month</span></div>
      <div>Status: <span class="text-white">● Maintained</span></div>
      <div>Team: <span class="text-white">1 Engineer</span></div>
      <div>Stack: <span class="text-white">WordPress · PHP · MySQL</span></div>
      <div>Repository: <span class="text-white">Private</span></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Case Study Sections -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- 1. Client Requirements -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">01. Client Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          The client required a website for 42 Holborn, a local dining venue. The operations staff had to update hours of operation, menu pdf lists, and table reservations booking links independently, without code edits or developer dependencies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Why WordPress -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">02. Why WordPress</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          WordPress was the correct technical decision here. While monolithic, it has zero learning curve for local operations staff who are already familiar with the WordPress dashboard. Introducing a modern headless framework would have created operational friction and added custom coding overhead for minor text adjustments.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Customizations -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">03. Customizations</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I built a custom child theme, disabling unused default plugins and Gutenberg blocks to ensure lightweight assets compilation. I also optimized database query footprints and implemented aggressive caching for static restaurant page layouts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Deployment -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">04. Deployment</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          The website was deployed on a managed Cloudways hosting instance, utilizing a global CDN cache layer to handle localized spikes in dining reservation traffic.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Lessons -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">05. Lessons</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I learned that the most advanced technology is not always the best tool for the job. Aligning framework decisions to the operational constraints of the client ensures system longevity and reduces developer maintenance overhead.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack footer (mono, last) -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-[#71717A] border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-6 mt-4">
      <span>Technologies: WordPress · PHP · MySQL · Apache</span>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
